race.comment: EVERAIN (4) resumed further improved, comfortably winning a 70 at Caulfield over 1400m as expected. Delivered at his only second-up outing and he can progress to better things this preparation. The one to beat. RESET THE JAZZ (1) is a well-performed galloper back in grade. Posted a decent number in an Open 3 two back at Geelong and was expected to follow it up in the rich VOBIS Gold Reef at Flemington, but disappointed. Has jumped out well since, and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. LARIO (9) was supported to win at Geelong but was a touch plain. Found more like his best winning there prior and he has a 2kg claim today and maps for the run of the race. Won his only start this track/distance and will hit this at peak and get every chance. OROVERO (10) and MOMETZ (6) are both each-way chances. The former has good upside and Craig William is a positive jockey engagement. The latter improved again winning a 70 at Pakenham and the 2kg claim brings him into it.
